Why is it on nearly every torrent I check there are always "zomg virus" comments? Wtf are you guys using, Norton?!

Anyway, this checks out clean. Uploader also has a whole string of apps to his name so I'm inclined to trust him over some random commenter.

For the clueless, to patch something means it's shouldn't be running or else windows won't let you patch it (common sense...). So: 1) Install, but don't run it. 2) Copy the crack to the installed folder. 3) Run crack, click Yes, wait for it to say done, then click No or just close it. 4) Delete crack. 5) You're good to go. Run the program, it shouldn't show the evaluation message anymore.

Btw, if you're doing this thing in somewhere not private, make sure your speaker volume is turned low or you've got headphones plugged in. The freaking crack patcher runs with this funky scene tune in the background - surprised the bejeezus outta me since I was at the office lol. Fortunately everybody else thought it was just some wanky cellphone ring tone before I managed to hit mute.
